I'm a fan of local bakeries and coffee shops, but for one of the big brands in the city, Pret A Manger is the best. It doubles as a coffee shop and cafe serving food specific to breakfast, lunch, and even dinner. For breakfast, they have fresh baked pastries from muffins to croissants (their hazelnut chocolate croissant is spot on), fresh fruit, egg sandwiches, and granola. For lunch, they have salads, wraps (cold and hot), soups. For dinner, they swap in even more wrap options.  The space is always clean and slick and service fast and efficient. This location has two rooms. The first is where you get your grab-and-go food. In and out. The other room is a medium sized dining room for those who want to stay.  If you are looking for a quick, cheaper bite to eat, Pret A Manger is a good option!
